    • Method Detail

      • Logout

        void Logout()
        Logout out the user. Logout the user and shows login gui and disposes current logs view.

      • openSecurity

        void openSecurity()
        Open security gui. Opens security gui and disposes current logs gui.

      • getAllLogs

        void getAllLogs()
        Get all logs. Tells the model to get all logs from database into a resultset and then loop through all log rows and prints them out in the logsview textarea.

      • openFileDialog

        void openFileDialog()
        Tells the model to open a file dialog. Tells the model to open a JFileChooser dialog and waits for user to select file. Then the model returns the data found in the selected file and then shows it in the logsview textarea.

      • deleteAllLogs

        void deleteAllLogs()
        Tells logsmodel to delete all logs.

      • deleteAllLogHistory

        void deleteAllLogHistory()
        Tells logsmodel to delete all log history.

      • getLogHistory

        void getLogHistory()
        Tells logsmodel to get all log history from database and then logsmodel turns it into a resultset and returns it here, then this method loops through all log history rows and print them out in the logsview textarea.

      • editLog

        void editLog()
        Tells logsmodel to edit log. Tells logmodel to ask user for edit input.

      • deleteLog

        Tells logsmodel to delete a certain log.

        void createNewLog()
        Tells logmodel to create a new log.

      • saveFileDialog

        private void saveFileDialog()
        Tells logmodel to open a JFileChooser dialog. With intent to save current logsview textarea data, it tells logmodel to open a JFileChooser dialog.

      • filterLogs

        void filterLogs()
        Tells logsmodel to filter logs from database. When logsmodel returns a resultset of the filtered logs by certain keywords given from the user input, this method will loop through the resultset and print out the filtered logs.
